700306f-a.title: Bronx: 192nd Street (West) - Jerome Avenue
700306f-a.text:
West 192nd Street, north side (houses thereon), between Jerome and Davidson Aves. The view is from an empty lot on the south side of the street and shows in the background the towers of the 258th Field
Artillery Armory.
January 30, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

701735f-a.title: Bronx: Jerome Avenue - 192nd Street (West)
701735f-a.text:
St. James Park: A view of a newly erected building on the east
side of Jerome Ave., at West 192nd Street.
January 30, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.

701343f-a.title: Bronx: Jerome Avenue - 192nd Street (West)
701343f-a.text:
Jerome Avenue, south from W. 192nd Street.
September 28, 1913
Gift of M. Vaxer

701344f-a.title: Bronx: Jerome Avenue - 192nd Street (West)
701344f-a.text:
Jerome Avenue, north from W. 192nd Street. On the right is
